WEBVTT

00:02.794 --> 00:04.504
We all lost something on our way here.

00:04.587 --> 00:07.424
I didn't lose my wife.
I know exactly where she was.

00:07.507 --> 00:09.843
She was in a different city
when it happened,

00:09.926 --> 00:12.595
and she died because he didn't get her
to a goddamn plane.

00:12.679 --> 00:15.015
[♪ pensive music playing]

00:16.224 --> 00:17.726
[Kane Bradford]
I saw her that night.

00:18.935 --> 00:20.395
I saw her.

00:22.188 --> 00:24.941
[Cal Bradford]
Got the news of the world right here.

00:25.775 --> 00:28.737
[Sinatra] [on recording]
Agent Pace, take them out.

00:28.820 --> 00:29.863
[gunshot]

00:31.573 --> 00:34.200
People need to know
that there are survivors,

00:34.284 --> 00:36.036
-and I'm gonna tell them the truth.
-No, you're not.

00:36.661 --> 00:39.330
[Xavier Collins]
First Cal, then Billy.

00:39.414 --> 00:40.415
It was her.

00:41.124 --> 00:42.125
[Robinson]
We take her down.

00:42.584 --> 00:45.295
It's gonna be hard taking
anybody down without weapons.

00:45.378 --> 00:48.131
-There are weapons.
-The sub-basement of the arena.

00:48.214 --> 00:51.676
You just punch in a code.
It's the day of my inauguration.

00:51.760 --> 00:52.886
And I know how to get 'em.

00:53.386 --> 00:56.222
Go upstairs and get your brother,
pack a bag,

00:56.306 --> 00:57.891
whatever you can fit into a backpack.

00:57.974 --> 01:00.518
Hey, Carl, I need to call in that favor.

01:00.602 --> 01:02.937
[♪ pensive music continues]

01:13.782 --> 01:15.950
[school bell ringing]

01:16.034 --> 01:20.455
My flight is still on time.
I need to finish packing.

01:20.538 --> 01:22.957
[students chattering]

01:23.041 --> 01:26.628
[sighs] Getting summoned
to the principal's office for a lecture

01:26.711 --> 01:29.339
-is the last thing I needed right now.
-Yeah, I know.

01:32.926 --> 01:34.594
She in trouble because of cake?

01:35.261 --> 01:36.638
Yeah, a shitload of cake.

01:41.768 --> 01:44.187
Hey, have you seen my blue jacket?
I need to pack it.

01:47.315 --> 01:48.316
What?

01:49.025 --> 01:51.111
Well, either you have
a problem with my jacket,

01:51.194 --> 01:53.655
-or you have a problem with me.
-I didn't say anything.

01:56.366 --> 01:58.326
My work takes me to Atlanta.

01:58.409 --> 02:00.495
-It's everything I've worked for, babe--
-I know.

02:04.124 --> 02:05.125
I know.

02:07.293 --> 02:09.671
Hey, if POTUS doesn't keep you
late again tonight,

02:09.754 --> 02:11.840
you could get home
in time to kiss me goodbye.

02:11.923 --> 02:13.842
Metro's been dicey this week.

02:14.509 --> 02:16.553
-Might even get a quickie.
-I'll be home by 5:00.

02:19.597 --> 02:20.640
[door opens]

02:21.766 --> 02:23.434
Mr. and Mrs. Collins.

02:23.518 --> 02:27.021
Mr. Collins
and, uh, Dr. Rogers-Collins, actually.

02:27.105 --> 02:29.023
Of course. Come in.

02:32.026 --> 02:35.238
Each eighth-grader
was asked to explore an issue

02:35.321 --> 02:38.074
that is negatively impacting
our world today.

02:38.158 --> 02:42.704
Presley's project was entitled
"An Exhibition of Food Inequality."

02:42.787 --> 02:45.206
-"Inequity."
-I'm sorry?

02:46.207 --> 02:49.586
The title of her project was
"An Exhibition of Food Inequity,"

02:49.669 --> 02:50.753
not "Inequality."

02:50.837 --> 02:54.299
Inequities are the result
of unjust inequalities.

02:54.382 --> 02:56.759
-They're not the same.
-Does the title matter?

02:56.843 --> 02:58.469
The project was a bunch of BS.

02:58.553 --> 02:59.888
-Excuse me?
-[Principal Dawes] Oh, boy.

02:59.971 --> 03:02.307
Okay, uh, we got the title. We're good.

03:03.308 --> 03:05.310
-Please continue.
-According to the teacher,

03:05.393 --> 03:09.856
Presley assigned each student a country
or a class of society to represent.

03:09.939 --> 03:12.609
She then passed out
one piece of cake to each student

03:12.692 --> 03:15.445
to show ideal global food security.

03:15.528 --> 03:18.239
Afterwards, she redistributed the cake

03:18.323 --> 03:21.826
to illustrate the current state
of food inequity.

03:21.910 --> 03:24.162
[Charlie's dad] Yeah, she made Charlie
a goddamn billionaire.

03:24.245 --> 03:27.373
She took the cake away from everybody else
and shoved it all at him.

03:27.457 --> 03:29.918
She had all children
representing poor countries

03:30.001 --> 03:31.336
chanting at him to eat.

03:31.419 --> 03:33.129
He ate so much cake--

03:33.213 --> 03:36.132
Alright, okay, well,
he didn't have to eat it.

03:36.216 --> 03:37.342
She was making a point.

03:37.425 --> 03:39.219
It was a nutjob project, and you know it.

03:39.302 --> 03:41.095
-My daughter is not a nutjob.
-Ter.

03:41.179 --> 03:43.806
Five years from now, you ask those kids
whose project made an impact--

03:43.890 --> 03:45.516
Mrs. Collins, that's not the point.

03:45.600 --> 03:46.809
That's not the point?

03:46.893 --> 03:49.020
-Presley will be issued a warning.
-Explore an issue,

03:49.103 --> 03:50.647
-that was the point, right?
-[Xavier sighs deeply]

03:50.730 --> 03:52.565
She explored the shit out of that issue.

03:52.649 --> 03:54.984
You wanted her to make a point,
she made the point.

03:55.068 --> 03:56.861
She made it so those kids
are gonna think twice

03:56.945 --> 03:59.113
before they toss
half their macaroni in the trash.

03:59.197 --> 04:00.740
-But you folks--
-Okay, Presley will be given

04:00.823 --> 04:02.408
a stern warning, we understand. Thank you.

04:02.492 --> 04:04.827
Charlie vomited in the garbage can.

04:04.911 --> 04:07.121
The kid's humiliated,
he's refusing to come to school.

04:07.205 --> 04:08.539
Hey, hey, here's a thought.

04:08.623 --> 04:10.875
Put his ass in the car
and tell him he's going to school.

04:10.959 --> 04:12.460
-Alright.
-Try that.

04:12.543 --> 04:14.879
He's gonna talk to me
about who's a goddamn nutjob.

04:14.963 --> 04:17.382
[sighs] It's good to see you, Cliff.

04:22.178 --> 04:24.514
[Teri chuckling]

04:24.597 --> 04:27.225
-You love me so much right now.
-Not even a little.

04:27.308 --> 04:28.476
[Teri laughing]

04:28.559 --> 04:30.520
The strings we pulled
to get her in this school,

04:31.145 --> 04:32.939
we can't be pissing off
the other parents like that.

04:33.022 --> 04:36.317
Oh, come on.
Those people call themselves parents?

04:36.401 --> 04:38.611
That Charlie is like a proper bully.

04:38.695 --> 04:41.447
Straight outta 1984.
He's old-school Cobra Kai.

04:41.531 --> 04:42.824
[Xavier chuckles]

04:42.907 --> 04:45.493
-The dirty duct tape incident?
-With the toilet water?

04:45.576 --> 04:46.786
-Uh-huh.
-That was that Charlie?

04:46.869 --> 04:48.454
-Uh-huh.
-I thought it was Charlie G

04:48.538 --> 04:50.415
-that was the bonehead.
-Yeah, no, it was him.

04:51.416 --> 04:53.251
X, your daughter
didn't just do a hell of a project.

04:53.334 --> 04:55.545
She pulled off the payback of the century.

04:55.628 --> 04:59.132
[sighs] You didn't need to make a scene.

04:59.674 --> 05:00.758
That's all I'm saying.

05:01.884 --> 05:05.555
Well, sometimes making a scene
is the only thing you need to do.

05:06.931 --> 05:11.102
Sweetheart, I love you.
You are the kindest, calmest,

05:11.185 --> 05:13.938
most centered human being on the planet.

05:14.022 --> 05:16.399
But one day, you are gonna hit your limit.

05:16.482 --> 05:19.694
[knife blade scraping]

05:19.777 --> 05:23.489
One day, some poor bastard
is gonna force you to make a scene.

05:23.573 --> 05:25.575
[knife blade continues scraping]

05:27.618 --> 05:30.413
And when that happens, tell you what...

05:31.289 --> 05:34.250
I would not want to be the motherfucker
on the other side of it.

05:34.334 --> 05:37.337
[♪ dramatic music playing]

05:40.131 --> 05:42.300
[knife blade continues scraping]

05:56.147 --> 05:57.815
[♪ music fades out]

06:00.443 --> 06:02.904
-[insects trilling]
-[clock ticking]

06:02.987 --> 06:04.322
Answer me this.

06:07.450 --> 06:09.535
How much cake did this kid
hold down before he yakked?

06:09.619 --> 06:11.287
[chuckling] At one point,

06:11.371 --> 06:13.915
Teri was looking like
she might take a swing at the dad.

06:14.499 --> 06:16.125
It's probably good
she's getting out of town.

06:18.252 --> 06:19.587
Atlanta again?

06:19.670 --> 06:21.756
Yeah, she's making big leaps at her job.

06:21.839 --> 06:24.634
She's, uh, she's amazing.

06:27.929 --> 06:29.972
Well, I'll leave you to it, sir.

06:34.310 --> 06:35.686
Hey, Collins, wait up.

06:35.770 --> 06:37.897
-Yes, sir?
-[glass clinking]

06:40.358 --> 06:42.276
Field trip. What do you say?

06:43.653 --> 06:46.489
It's getting late.
You don't wanna finish up here?

06:48.533 --> 06:50.326
-What's there to do?
-[paper stack thuds]

06:50.410 --> 06:51.869
It's all unfixable.

06:55.206 --> 06:57.583
I want you to walk me through
the Versailles protocol.

06:58.835 --> 07:00.837
Where do they take me
if the shit hits the fan?

07:01.838 --> 07:04.257
I mean, I know you don't know
any of the details

07:04.340 --> 07:07.468
about what the actual shit might be
and when it could hit said fan.

07:07.552 --> 07:10.179
But from a logistical standpoint,
how do they get me outta here?

07:10.263 --> 07:13.474
-You know the protocol.
-I don't, actually.

07:15.059 --> 07:16.436
Marsha, you wanna come in here?

07:19.230 --> 07:20.940
Xavier's gonna take me on a little walk.

07:21.482 --> 07:22.650
We can call it a night.

07:22.733 --> 07:24.485
Sounds good, Mr. President.

07:24.569 --> 07:26.863
Don't keep him up too late, Xavier,
it's a school night.

07:26.946 --> 07:28.197
That's a promise.

07:29.574 --> 07:32.577
[people chattering]

07:39.459 --> 07:42.462
[♪ dramatic music playing]

07:49.719 --> 07:51.095
[wristband chimes]

07:51.179 --> 07:53.139
[bollards whirring]

07:58.019 --> 08:00.688
Why are there still words on my sky?
You said you were on it.

08:01.272 --> 08:02.648
Turns out we can't take them down.

08:02.732 --> 08:03.941
What do you mean you can't?

08:04.025 --> 08:05.735
Whoever did this
locked us out of the system.

08:07.445 --> 08:10.448
[♪ pensive music playing]

08:16.704 --> 08:18.414
-[Mark] Carl Jenkins?
-Oh!

08:19.290 --> 08:20.750
Yes.

08:20.833 --> 08:23.419
Yes. And this is Lucy.

08:23.878 --> 08:25.546
What the fuck.
How'd you get a dog down here?

08:25.630 --> 08:28.257
It's why Xavier wants me to hide,
in case they go searching.

08:28.799 --> 08:29.967
Where do I go?

08:30.051 --> 08:33.304
All I know is he said to stay put.
Safest thing is to have you all here.

08:33.387 --> 08:35.014
The kids are in the back room.

08:42.980 --> 08:44.190
[James Collins]
What are you doing?

08:46.901 --> 08:48.569
-[bag zipping]
-You're leaving?

08:48.653 --> 08:50.613
Dad told us to stay here
until he came back for us.

08:50.696 --> 08:51.739
I know what he said.

08:53.074 --> 08:54.325
But, James, listen to me.

08:55.409 --> 08:57.912
You know how you're always begging me
to let you do cool shit?

08:59.830 --> 09:02.166
Well, I'm gonna need you
to do some cool shit for me.

09:04.418 --> 09:07.004
♪♪

09:09.590 --> 09:10.591
Thank you.

09:11.509 --> 09:13.344
It's quite the scene out there. [chuckles]

09:15.221 --> 09:16.722
Let's cut the bullshit.

09:18.266 --> 09:19.642
Let's, yes, um...

09:21.852 --> 09:25.106
Well, I'm glad that you called me in,
because whatever's going on out there,

09:25.189 --> 09:27.191
we're gonna need some
carefully crafted messaging

09:27.275 --> 09:29.110
to calm the collective anxiety
of all of the--

09:29.193 --> 09:31.028
I'm sorry, I thought we just agreed
to cut the bullshit.

09:32.405 --> 09:33.739
"Whatever's going on out there"?

09:34.824 --> 09:37.326
Agent Collins is what's going on,
so no need for us

09:37.410 --> 09:39.161
to act like we don't know what's what.

09:40.413 --> 09:41.539
Xavier?

09:45.209 --> 09:46.419
Wowza.

09:49.839 --> 09:52.091
Screw a guy in the shower,
and he doesn't even tell you

09:52.174 --> 09:54.385
when he's gonna topple
the city-wide status quo.

09:54.468 --> 09:57.096
[exhales sharply] Men, am I right?

10:01.726 --> 10:06.856
I... I picked you up
off the floor, Samantha.

10:07.315 --> 10:09.650
You violated the privacy of my home?

10:09.734 --> 10:10.901
Here's the thing.

10:12.403 --> 10:15.740
You love this city. I love this city.

10:16.782 --> 10:18.409
If we want to preserve it,

10:19.327 --> 10:21.746
you need to go have a nice meal
with your man

10:21.829 --> 10:23.914
and find out what he's up to.

10:24.540 --> 10:26.250
He just checked in at the diner.

10:36.302 --> 10:37.595
Strange out there, huh?

10:39.388 --> 10:41.974
The last time you were in,
you barely touched your cheese fries.

10:42.058 --> 10:43.768
You wanna try again?

10:43.851 --> 10:45.686
I'm good with the steak, thanks.

10:47.730 --> 10:49.690
[door bell jingling]

10:55.821 --> 10:58.366
You know, I thought
I was gonna miss real meat more.

10:59.742 --> 11:01.827
I actually don't mind
this plant-based stuff.

11:02.662 --> 11:06.207
-Puts on a pretty convincing show.
-Xavier.

11:06.290 --> 11:07.667
Plus, there's this thing...

11:08.709 --> 11:11.128
it has been caught in my head, Doc.

11:11.212 --> 11:13.464
It was this thing from before.

11:14.924 --> 11:17.009
Before the world ended,
when we used to eat real meat.

11:19.053 --> 11:23.015
I can't stop thinking about how they used
to catch the cows to butcher them.

11:23.099 --> 11:26.102
[♪ dramatic music playing]

11:28.396 --> 11:31.023
And back then, you wouldn't let
your mind go there, but now...

11:32.274 --> 11:33.943
can't stop thinking about it.

11:34.902 --> 11:37.154
[♪ dramatic music continues]

11:38.197 --> 11:41.826
I can picture it,
what it must've looked like...

11:42.868 --> 11:44.078
sounded like.

11:45.621 --> 11:46.997
[keypad beeping]

11:47.081 --> 11:48.207
How they corralled them,

11:49.083 --> 11:51.585
and they shrank the space
smaller and smaller

11:51.669 --> 11:53.671
until the animals broke.

12:03.055 --> 12:06.392
They would line up single-file

12:06.475 --> 12:08.686
and march down a chute to their death.

12:15.526 --> 12:19.613
All that muscle, all that heft,
and they just surrendered.

12:22.032 --> 12:25.494
And it makes you wonder
if that's what she did to us.

12:27.121 --> 12:31.500
Led us down here, corralled us,
and sent us to slaughter.

12:33.794 --> 12:37.173
Xavier, what's going on? What happened?

12:41.135 --> 12:42.803
The president is dead.

12:44.597 --> 12:47.183
Billy Pace is dead.

12:48.434 --> 12:50.895
And now, here you are.

12:53.314 --> 12:56.734
So, why don't you tell me what happened?

12:57.568 --> 12:59.862
Why did she kill them?

13:01.322 --> 13:05.201
Xavier, Samantha Redmond
is a lot of things.

13:05.284 --> 13:07.912
-Mm-hmm.
-She's wildly imperfect.

13:08.913 --> 13:10.664
But she's not a monster.

13:12.792 --> 13:16.879
She's a mother, and she's trying
to protect the people in her charge.

13:16.962 --> 13:18.839
Well, what did she think of the sky?

13:22.384 --> 13:23.469
I did it for her.

13:26.639 --> 13:29.350
-She's trying to take it down.
-Yeah, no shit.

13:29.433 --> 13:31.352
[phone buzzing]

13:31.435 --> 13:33.229
[utensils clattering]

13:37.399 --> 13:38.651
What is it?

13:38.734 --> 13:41.737
[♪ dramatic music continues]

13:49.870 --> 13:50.955
[grunts]

13:56.961 --> 13:59.171
-[wristband ripping]
-[electricity fizzles]

14:03.425 --> 14:04.927
Tell your girl I'm comin' for her.

14:10.224 --> 14:11.308
[door bell jingling]

14:17.189 --> 14:18.607
[Xavier]
If Versailles protocol is launched,

14:18.691 --> 14:21.318
this is the most direct route
to the West Wing PEOC.

14:28.701 --> 14:30.369
You know, the first time
I saw that, I thought,

14:30.452 --> 14:33.122
what the hell kinda gift is that
to the White House?

14:33.831 --> 14:35.708
Two old women reading books.

14:37.501 --> 14:39.086
Then you look a little closer...

14:41.171 --> 14:43.549
and you realize
they're just passing time...

14:45.342 --> 14:46.927
covered by mosquito nets.

14:48.304 --> 14:50.681
Fooling themselves into thinking
there's anything they can do

14:50.764 --> 14:53.142
to protect from the violence of nature.

14:59.607 --> 15:02.192
-Good evening, sir.
-General.

15:04.570 --> 15:05.738
Hey.

15:05.821 --> 15:08.407
Well, you're in a hurry tonight.
You got someplace to be?

15:08.490 --> 15:10.451
Thought you wanted the tour.

15:10.534 --> 15:13.787
Southwest staircase
also has restricted access.

15:13.871 --> 15:16.415
West Wing bunker's five flights down.

15:16.498 --> 15:17.541
Okay.

15:18.250 --> 15:20.461
-Hang on. Hang on.
-[scanner chirping]

15:22.087 --> 15:23.505
A little stress reliever.

15:23.589 --> 15:25.925
-[foot stomping]
-Yeah, I know.

15:26.008 --> 15:28.218
John McClane
didn't believe it at first either.

15:29.345 --> 15:32.431
Die Hard, you make little fists
with your toes, remember?

15:32.514 --> 15:33.641
Never saw it.

15:34.725 --> 15:36.602
You never seen Die Hard?

15:38.395 --> 15:41.065
That's a bridge too far, Collins.
We're gonna have to remedy that.

15:41.148 --> 15:43.192
-Yes, sir.
-Alright.

15:44.026 --> 15:45.027
Where would we go next?

15:47.154 --> 15:49.823
[indistinct chatter]

15:50.824 --> 15:53.202
He said the message
in the sky was for you.

15:55.204 --> 15:56.580
He said he was coming for you.

15:57.164 --> 15:58.666
Who the hell talks like that?

15:59.541 --> 16:02.044
Then he hacks off his band with a knife?

16:02.127 --> 16:05.255
What the fuck is he doing?
I mean, besides dramatically eating.

16:07.925 --> 16:09.635
He was waiting at that diner.

16:11.804 --> 16:14.223
Waiting for me to send someone. Morton?

16:14.306 --> 16:16.392
-Ma'am?
-Any information on his kids?

16:16.475 --> 16:18.394
-Um...
-[keyboard clacking]

16:19.269 --> 16:21.522
He must have removed their bands, too.

16:21.605 --> 16:23.899
-Who else is offline?
-Band removal happens more than you think.

16:23.983 --> 16:26.276
Any given moment,
there's usually a couple dozen or more.

16:27.027 --> 16:28.988
Any of them known associates
of Xavier Collins?

16:29.071 --> 16:30.656
Known associates...

16:30.739 --> 16:33.200
A member of his team, Melvin Rainey.

16:33.283 --> 16:35.411
And the special agent in charge
of the Secret Service detail,

16:35.494 --> 16:36.829
Nicole Robinson.

16:38.664 --> 16:40.249
You think they're helping him?

16:40.332 --> 16:42.084
Before Robinson's wristband went offline,
she used it

16:42.167 --> 16:45.004
to access the southeast sub-basement door.

16:48.924 --> 16:49.925
The weapons.

16:51.677 --> 16:53.846
Go keep an eye on my family. Now.

17:00.352 --> 17:03.897
[♪ dramatic music playing]

17:31.425 --> 17:34.428
♪♪

17:46.315 --> 17:48.317
Shit. It's me.

17:49.485 --> 17:50.652
Sorry.

17:52.321 --> 17:54.364
It does feel good to have it back though.

17:54.448 --> 17:58.160
The weight, that recoil,
brass flipping through the air.

17:58.869 --> 18:00.954
-You need a moment?
-I'm good.

18:02.372 --> 18:03.957
[Xavier]
Alright, who we got?

18:04.541 --> 18:07.086
Well, Garcia was in from go.

18:07.169 --> 18:08.378
Brooks.

18:08.462 --> 18:11.507
Told them both to get together
a crew of folks they trust,

18:11.590 --> 18:13.467
folks who know how to handle themselves.

18:14.051 --> 18:15.302
They'll be here any minute.

18:15.385 --> 18:17.429
-Should be enough manpower.
-Good.

18:17.513 --> 18:19.431
[gun clicking]

18:20.224 --> 18:22.768
What about Jane? She with us?

18:22.851 --> 18:24.103
You see her yesterday?

18:24.186 --> 18:27.272
She was practically catatonic over Pace.
I didn't even bother.

18:27.356 --> 18:30.067
She's loyal. She'd be an asset.

18:30.150 --> 18:31.819
Xavier, even on her best day,

18:31.902 --> 18:34.071
she's barely a notch
above a fucking intern.

18:34.154 --> 18:36.406
She's Holly Hobbie with a gun.

18:36.490 --> 18:39.660
-How much time we got?
-It should be starting soon.

18:44.289 --> 18:46.166
Why the fuck is he talking
like Santa Claus?

18:46.250 --> 18:47.584
It's a Die Hard reference, ma'am.

18:48.627 --> 18:51.630
[amplified ticking outside]

18:58.178 --> 19:00.848
[♪ dramatic music continues]

19:00.931 --> 19:02.141
[ticking stops]

19:10.274 --> 19:12.109
[Morton] We don't know
what the subsequent messages are,

19:12.192 --> 19:13.569
or when they might appear.

19:13.652 --> 19:15.696
What we do know,
is the sky seems to be cycling

19:15.779 --> 19:18.031
through some kind of locked program.

19:19.116 --> 19:20.284
He's taunting you.

19:21.410 --> 19:24.079
He's threatening to expose something.
What does he have on you?

19:24.163 --> 19:25.747
I want it fixed.

19:25.831 --> 19:28.375
I want it off the sky now,
whatever it takes.

19:28.458 --> 19:31.003
Ma'am, we don't have a clear path
to overriding this program.

19:31.670 --> 19:34.256
The only other option is a hard reboot.

19:34.798 --> 19:36.842
We shut down the sky and turn it back on.

19:36.925 --> 19:38.552
[sighs] How long?

19:40.262 --> 19:41.555
Beverly?

19:41.638 --> 19:43.724
We don't know.
It's never been done before.

19:45.934 --> 19:46.977
Absolutely not.

19:47.060 --> 19:50.564
Sam, a shutdown would be like
reliving everything all over again.

19:50.647 --> 19:54.109
The sheltering protocols,
the illusion of world being broken.

19:54.776 --> 19:56.028
The sky would go out.

19:56.653 --> 19:59.489
People would remember
they are living in a cave.

19:59.573 --> 20:02.326
-They know they're living in a cave.
-Okay, okay, listen, ha--

20:02.409 --> 20:05.370
have you ever been on a ride
at Disneyland when it breaks down?

20:05.454 --> 20:09.458
They turn on the lights, and then
it is never the same for you again.

20:10.459 --> 20:13.086
Samantha, look at me. Look at me.

20:14.922 --> 20:16.048
Find Xavier.

20:16.131 --> 20:17.591
You can work this out.

20:18.842 --> 20:20.552
[♪ dramatic music playing]

20:25.891 --> 20:27.893
[technicians chattering]

20:29.394 --> 20:31.271
Reboot isn't an option.

20:31.355 --> 20:33.190
Find another way to disable the program.

20:33.273 --> 20:34.566
Yes, ma'am.

20:36.526 --> 20:38.070
I want all authorities alerted.

20:38.153 --> 20:40.906
Be on the lookout for Collins.
Arrest him on sight.

20:40.989 --> 20:42.074
Copy that.

20:44.660 --> 20:45.661
[sirens chirping]

20:46.245 --> 20:47.663
[text chimes]

20:47.746 --> 20:49.957
[♪ dramatic music playing]

20:56.546 --> 20:57.714
[phone chimes]

21:21.446 --> 21:24.324
-It was nice to lose the bracelet.
-Appreciate you, Garcia.

21:24.408 --> 21:26.201
All of you. Hey, man.

21:26.285 --> 21:29.413
Pace was an asshole,
but he didn't off himself.

21:29.496 --> 21:32.249
So, think you can handle this thing?

21:34.626 --> 21:36.086
[gun clicking]

21:36.169 --> 21:38.046
Five years in the SEALs
before I got fat, baby.

21:38.547 --> 21:39.631
[Rainey chuckles]

21:39.715 --> 21:41.591
-They got a BOLO out on you.
-[Xavier] Good.

21:41.675 --> 21:43.302
It means she's taking the bait.

21:43.844 --> 21:45.804
Weapons stay outta sight
as much as possible.

21:45.887 --> 21:47.180
We're not trying to panic the people.

21:47.264 --> 21:49.599
-Last resort only.
-[Rainey] Hey, look, I am all in.

21:49.683 --> 21:51.685
But how the fuck are we gonna
pull this off without firing?

21:52.561 --> 21:54.313
Just a little bit of magic, Rainey.

21:55.522 --> 21:57.733
[Trent] I appreciate you
taking advantage of this place.

21:57.816 --> 22:00.444
Most people never set foot in here.

22:01.445 --> 22:03.655
Yeah, well, I just, uh,
I just like the music.

22:04.781 --> 22:06.742
Well, if you're, uh, interested,

22:06.825 --> 22:08.869
you should really check out
our exhibit on the bunker design.

22:08.952 --> 22:10.704
You know what, I'm gonna--
I'm gonna turn on the lights...

22:10.787 --> 22:12.122
[voice fading out]

22:12.205 --> 22:16.168
[♪ "Knockin' on Heaven's Door"
plays on headphones]

22:20.464 --> 22:22.257
Dude, I really don't care how this...

22:22.341 --> 22:23.967
How can you just be sitting here?

22:24.968 --> 22:26.345
Weird stuff is happening.

22:27.471 --> 22:30.307
-And I need to tell you something.
-Okay.

22:34.311 --> 22:36.813
Billy is dead, and...

22:39.024 --> 22:42.986
I don't know what my dad is doing,
but I think it might be because of this.

22:45.322 --> 22:46.656
Where did you find that?

22:48.241 --> 22:52.204
[sighs] Sometimes I went to your dad's
to play Wii with Billy,

22:52.287 --> 22:54.122
because they'd turn the cameras off.

22:54.873 --> 22:58.877
That's what I was doing,
I was going there that night.

23:00.337 --> 23:04.174
I was heading inside,
and it was just laying there.

23:05.509 --> 23:06.510
[tablet chimes]

23:08.136 --> 23:09.971
I shouldn't have taken it, but...

23:11.056 --> 23:13.517
I thought maybe it could tell me
something about my mom,

23:14.184 --> 23:15.852
about what happened in Atlanta.

23:17.646 --> 23:19.898
Maybe if I knew what happened to her...

23:21.983 --> 23:24.152
it won't feel so much like she died alone.

23:27.072 --> 23:28.156
But it's protected.

23:30.033 --> 23:32.911
I couldn't even get the stupid thing
to open to give me that much.

23:37.874 --> 23:39.000
I can help.

23:41.461 --> 23:44.047
They told you the president
died of natural causes.

23:45.424 --> 23:48.760
I saw the body. I saw the blood.

23:50.595 --> 23:52.264
President Bradford was murdered.

23:54.474 --> 23:56.435
Many of you knew Agent Billy Pace...

23:58.311 --> 24:00.397
and they told you he killed himself.

24:01.481 --> 24:02.774
And that's a lie, too.

24:05.193 --> 24:09.531
Samantha Redmond,
code name Sinatra, is behind this.

24:10.657 --> 24:12.242
She's pulling the strings,

24:12.325 --> 24:14.536
and the other billionaires
are marching in step.

24:15.704 --> 24:16.872
But that ends now...

24:18.039 --> 24:20.000
'cause we're taking control of the city.

24:21.501 --> 24:24.463
And when we do, we will find justice...

24:25.464 --> 24:28.216
for the president, for Billy,

24:28.300 --> 24:31.428
and for every one of us
who went through hell to get here.

24:33.263 --> 24:36.558
Because we didn't come this far
to be fed a bunch of lies.

24:37.767 --> 24:40.979
We didn't come this far
to nod our heads and play along.

24:42.606 --> 24:46.776
So, if you're with me,
we're gonna go out there

24:47.402 --> 24:49.946
and we're gonna rip the fucking lies
right from underneath 'em.

24:50.030 --> 24:52.282
-[agent] Let's go!
-We're gonna make a scene.

24:53.325 --> 24:54.326
You know why?

24:55.660 --> 24:59.080
Because sometimes making a scene
is the only thing you need to do.

25:05.921 --> 25:08.256
All staff cleared for Versailles
have biometric access

25:08.340 --> 25:09.674
to the West Wing bunker.

25:09.758 --> 25:11.259
[elevator doors hissing]

25:11.343 --> 25:14.513
Huh, nothing like being
hermetically sealed.

25:14.596 --> 25:17.974
Hey, I say we lock the VP out as a joke.
You imagine the look on his face?

25:18.058 --> 25:20.727
On the day, a special agent
in charge of evacuation

25:20.810 --> 25:23.396
will escort our group to Marine One.

25:23.480 --> 25:26.399
Now, the bunker was built
to withstand a direct nuclear hit.

25:26.483 --> 25:28.568
It has a self-contained
food and air supply

25:28.652 --> 25:31.571
that will support the entire
West Wing indefinitely.

25:31.655 --> 25:34.699
-Interesting.
-But no one's gonna be camping out here.

25:34.783 --> 25:37.160
The minute Versailles is called,
you record the speech,

25:37.244 --> 25:40.372
we're escorted down,
wait for confirmation of the safest route

25:40.455 --> 25:42.582
to Joint Base Andrews, then we're out.

25:42.666 --> 25:45.502
So, go to finish,
the whole thing is what, 30, 40 minutes?

25:45.585 --> 25:47.671
Ideally? Versailles, to bunker,

25:47.754 --> 25:51.299
to South Lawn tunnel, to Marine One,
to Andrews, to Air Force One,

25:51.383 --> 25:53.426
20 minutes tops, and then we're airborne.

25:53.510 --> 25:55.387
And then we soar off to Xanadu.

25:55.470 --> 25:56.805
[Xavier sighs]

25:59.808 --> 26:00.934
What?

26:01.977 --> 26:03.937
Sir, I'd like to know what's happening,

26:04.646 --> 26:06.398
and I'd like to know when it's happening.

26:07.482 --> 26:09.859
I know it's not my place to ask,
but I'm asking.

26:10.860 --> 26:13.738
When does this mysterious shit
hit the fan,

26:13.822 --> 26:15.532
and where exactly are we going?

26:21.162 --> 26:22.163
I can't.

26:29.713 --> 26:30.714
Collins...

26:33.717 --> 26:36.136
I think it's time you put
your foot down with your wife.

26:37.971 --> 26:41.683
Trips to Atlanta are not as risk-free
as they used to be.

26:44.269 --> 26:46.896
My wife hasn't listened
to me for 20 years, sir.

26:47.939 --> 26:51.735
I have no details.
It all sounds so far-fetched.

26:52.944 --> 26:54.279
[Cal sighs]

26:55.280 --> 26:56.364
Okay.

26:57.949 --> 26:59.534
Well, then, if it comes to that...

27:01.453 --> 27:04.164
I guess we'll just have to go
pick her up from there.

27:04.247 --> 27:06.708
[♪ solemn music playing]

27:16.593 --> 27:19.220
I'm gonna be the man in charge
when the world ends.

27:25.226 --> 27:26.936
[gun clicking]

27:27.020 --> 27:28.897
[indistinct chatter]

27:28.980 --> 27:30.231
Feels good, doesn't it?

27:32.609 --> 27:35.570
Stay vigilant, watch your squads,
get to your assigned posts.

27:35.654 --> 27:37.656
Robinson and I are going
for the explosives.

27:37.739 --> 27:39.991
You telling me we got RPGs
stashed somewhere around here?

27:40.075 --> 27:42.494
Nope. Just a little bit of magic, Rainey.

27:42.577 --> 27:44.079
-[Robinson chuckles]
-Let's move!

27:44.162 --> 27:45.622
Alpha, on me!

27:45.705 --> 27:48.416
-Move it!
-Alright, you heard him, let's move.

27:48.500 --> 27:49.918
[indistinct shouting]

27:52.462 --> 27:55.799
[Sinatra] What's written on the sky
is cycling through a locked program.

27:55.882 --> 27:57.592
Reboot isn't an option.

27:57.676 --> 28:00.387
The effects on the population
would be too costly.

28:00.762 --> 28:03.348
Our techs are finding another way
to disable the program.

28:03.431 --> 28:07.310
You keep saying "program."
The message is going to change again?

28:07.394 --> 28:08.853
We don't know. It's possible.

28:08.937 --> 28:11.064
The sky is the least of our problems.

28:11.564 --> 28:15.318
Can we address the fact that some agent
breached the goddamn weapons cache?

28:15.402 --> 28:16.945
-[billionaires clamoring]
-I'm sorry, what agent?

28:17.028 --> 28:18.822
How does he know about the weapons?

28:18.905 --> 28:20.573
[billionaire 1]
Samantha, what do you know about this?

28:20.657 --> 28:22.659
[billionaire 2] We are sitting ducks here.
What does he want?

28:22.742 --> 28:25.745
[clamoring continues]

28:27.372 --> 28:29.165
[billionaire 3]
How many people does he have?

28:29.249 --> 28:30.709
[♪ dramatic music playing]

28:30.792 --> 28:32.127
[billionaire 4]
How are we containing this?

28:33.753 --> 28:36.756
[clamoring continues]

28:36.840 --> 28:38.299
[door closes]

28:38.800 --> 28:40.093
[♪ music softens]

28:40.176 --> 28:42.178
[breathing deeply]

28:48.685 --> 28:51.563
[♪ dramatic music resumes]

28:52.772 --> 28:53.940
[phone beeping]

29:10.123 --> 29:13.126
[♪ dramatic music continues]

29:28.391 --> 29:30.268
[voice echoing]
Provide stability.

29:30.351 --> 29:32.604
We may all come from different worlds,

29:32.687 --> 29:35.064
but we are all on the same team now.

29:37.776 --> 29:39.027
[Xavier] You good?

29:39.778 --> 29:41.070
[exhales sharply]

29:42.322 --> 29:44.407
I haven't been back here
since the day we arrived.

29:46.034 --> 29:49.287
I was so busy barking out orders,
I never even really...

29:49.370 --> 29:50.538
[breathing heavily]

29:50.622 --> 29:52.665
[inaudible]

29:55.710 --> 29:58.338
That day... you know? I'm...

29:59.255 --> 30:00.507
-I'm sorry.
-It's cool.

30:01.049 --> 30:02.634
We're cool. Come on.

30:04.344 --> 30:05.428
[grunts]

30:08.097 --> 30:11.100
[♪ dramatic music playing]

30:15.939 --> 30:17.148
[wristband chimes]

30:20.902 --> 30:21.986
[Jeremy Bradford]
Grandpa?

30:26.491 --> 30:28.535
The words, they, uh...

30:29.202 --> 30:31.830
[chuckles] They pour through.

30:32.413 --> 30:34.332
If I had a cup, I could catch 'em.

30:35.917 --> 30:39.629
Well, um, Grandpa, this is--
this is Presley.

30:39.712 --> 30:40.713
Remember her?

30:41.840 --> 30:44.050
You were right,
you-- you did see her here before,

30:44.133 --> 30:46.261
but she wasn't doing anything bad.

30:46.344 --> 30:48.304
Um, see, I'm-I'm trying to help her.

30:48.388 --> 30:49.806
She's-- she's, um...

30:50.974 --> 30:52.183
She's important to me.

30:54.894 --> 30:56.312
Look, Grandpa...

30:57.730 --> 31:01.317
we're trying to, um,
we're trying to get this open.

31:02.777 --> 31:03.820
Can you help?

31:06.656 --> 31:09.534
[Xavier] You get stationed on
Air Force One, you memorize all the stats.

31:10.201 --> 31:13.538
Like that the underbelly of this thing
is filled with defensive measures,

31:13.621 --> 31:17.709
including flares capable of misguiding
a targeted missile when deployed.

31:18.376 --> 31:21.671
We don't have to blow shit up, Robinson.
We just need her to think we are.

31:22.672 --> 31:24.674
-[grunting]
-[Garcia] [over comms] Garcia for Collins.

31:25.341 --> 31:26.426
Go for Collins.

31:26.509 --> 31:27.677
[Garcia]
Weapons secure.

31:27.760 --> 31:29.095
How we doing on the magic?

31:30.346 --> 31:31.556
We're about to bring it.

31:32.807 --> 31:33.808
[Jeremy] Grandpa?

31:38.104 --> 31:41.733
It's not that simple, Cal. Never was.

31:46.696 --> 31:48.156
I've seen that before.

31:49.532 --> 31:50.825
I saw it that night.

31:51.492 --> 31:53.661
[♪ mysterious music playing]

31:56.998 --> 31:58.666
I wanna help you, son.

31:58.750 --> 32:00.293
-But...
-Okay, yeah.

32:01.294 --> 32:02.378
Yeah.

32:06.299 --> 32:09.302
[tablet beeping and chiming]

32:20.313 --> 32:21.481
Thank you.

32:29.572 --> 32:32.742
[♪ solemn music playing]

32:43.586 --> 32:46.089
[footsteps]

32:48.716 --> 32:50.677
[Gabriela Torabi]
You're doing the right thing.

32:55.181 --> 32:56.224
[Sinatra exhales sharply]

33:01.771 --> 33:03.982
Hadley has a biology test today.

33:06.067 --> 33:07.860
She's really been studying for it.

33:08.987 --> 33:10.405
We were up late prepping.

33:13.783 --> 33:15.702
It's amazing how much time
we spend studying

33:15.785 --> 33:17.829
just to forget everything when we grow up.

33:22.583 --> 33:25.253
You're doing the right thing
waiting this out.

33:26.295 --> 33:27.714
-[sighs]
-The police will find Xavier,

33:27.797 --> 33:29.340
and then you can talk to him.

33:30.591 --> 33:32.010
Find a resolution.

33:35.096 --> 33:36.973
Do you really think that's possible?

33:47.400 --> 33:48.568
What does he know?

33:56.159 --> 33:57.577
What? Did you find something?

33:58.661 --> 34:00.913
There's stuff about Atlanta on here.

34:02.582 --> 34:04.667
Two thermonuclear weapons hit there.

34:06.878 --> 34:08.629
And I found something else.

34:11.758 --> 34:14.010
[Gabriela]
What are you afraid of him exposing?

34:14.969 --> 34:16.012
Samantha.

34:17.472 --> 34:18.681
What did you do?

34:19.974 --> 34:22.101
♪ The way you wear your hat ♪

34:22.185 --> 34:25.021
[♪ "They Can't Take That Away From Me"
by Frank Sinatra plays over loudspeakers]

34:25.104 --> 34:27.356
♪ The way you sip your tea ♪

34:29.025 --> 34:31.360
♪ The memory of all that ♪

34:33.571 --> 34:37.325
♪ No, no, they can't
take that away from me ♪

34:37.408 --> 34:40.828
♪ The way your smile just beams ♪

34:41.996 --> 34:44.082
♪ The way you sing off-key ♪

34:44.165 --> 34:45.875
[amplified timer ticking]

34:45.958 --> 34:49.087
♪ The way you haunt my dreams ♪

34:50.421 --> 34:54.759
♪ No, no, they can't
take that away from me ♪

34:54.842 --> 34:57.303
Boss! Cleared a spot for you.

34:57.386 --> 35:00.139
[crowd chattering]

35:00.223 --> 35:04.143
♪ On that bumpy road to love ♪

35:06.979 --> 35:09.440
The music is a part of the locked program.
We can't turn it off.

35:10.733 --> 35:12.610
♪ You can't take that away from me ♪

35:12.693 --> 35:16.030
♪ The way your smile just beams ♪

35:17.573 --> 35:20.326
♪ The way you sing off-key ♪

35:21.452 --> 35:23.788
♪ The way you haunt my dreams ♪

35:23.871 --> 35:26.499
[crowd]
Ten, nine, eight,

35:26.582 --> 35:29.210
seven, six, five,

35:29.293 --> 35:31.838
four, three,

35:31.921 --> 35:33.965
two, one.

35:34.048 --> 35:35.508
[fireworks exploding]

35:35.591 --> 35:36.926
-[people shouting]
-Get down, ma'am!

35:38.094 --> 35:39.679
-[flares blasting]
-[people screaming]

35:40.638 --> 35:42.306
[flares booming]

35:42.390 --> 35:45.393
[♪ dramatic music playing]

35:50.106 --> 35:52.483
-[echoing] Morton.
-[echoing] Samantha, wait.

35:52.567 --> 35:54.694
[normal]
Shut it down. Shut it all down.

35:54.777 --> 35:56.279
[booming continues]

35:56.362 --> 35:59.198
[♪ dramatic music playing]

36:00.825 --> 36:03.411
♪♪

36:13.087 --> 36:15.089
[power surging]

36:16.632 --> 36:18.718
-[panels banging]
-[people gasping]

36:18.801 --> 36:20.553
[people shouting, gasping]

36:20.636 --> 36:23.181
[♪ somber music playing]

36:24.015 --> 36:25.016
[lights clicking]

36:25.099 --> 36:26.726
[breathing heavily]

36:34.817 --> 36:36.611
[alarm blaring]

36:36.694 --> 36:40.698
[people clamoring]

36:46.704 --> 36:48.998
Yippee-ki-yay, motherfucker.

36:54.795 --> 36:57.465
Listen, the bunker tour
was 11 out of 10, really.

36:57.965 --> 36:59.717
You even walked me home. I'm blushing.

36:59.800 --> 37:01.135
-[softly chuckles]
-[door closes]

37:01.219 --> 37:04.889
But, I gotta tell you,
I really undersold Die Hard.

37:04.972 --> 37:07.099
You gotta see it, man,
it's not all about feet.

37:07.183 --> 37:08.267
Yes, sir.

37:08.351 --> 37:10.770
-You off the clock?
-About to be, sir.

37:10.853 --> 37:13.814
Metro's been dicey, want to get home
before Teri heads out.

37:13.898 --> 37:14.982
She leaves tonight?

37:15.608 --> 37:17.318
Yes, sir, I told you.

37:17.401 --> 37:19.612
No, you told me she was leaving.
You didn't say she was leaving tonight.

37:19.695 --> 37:21.322
Fuck the metro, I'm gonna get you a car.

37:21.405 --> 37:23.074
I appreciate that, sir, thank you.

37:23.157 --> 37:25.743
Alright, well, just do yourself a favor
and watch the movie, will ya?

37:25.826 --> 37:27.370
You'll be all about Hans Gruber.

37:27.453 --> 37:29.914
He's the bad guy,
but he's classy-smart like you.

37:30.498 --> 37:32.583
You think he's doing one thing,
but really, he's just getting the FBI

37:32.667 --> 37:34.377
to play right into his hand.

37:34.460 --> 37:37.255
Yeah, can we get our boy Xavier
a car, STAT?

37:37.338 --> 37:38.339
Thank you.

37:38.422 --> 37:39.757
-[alarm blaring]
-[automated voice] Reboot initiated.

37:39.840 --> 37:41.384
Commence shelter protocol.

37:41.884 --> 37:42.969
Return to your homes...

37:43.052 --> 37:44.929
Shelter protocol. Let's move, now.

37:45.012 --> 37:46.097
Stay low. This way.

37:46.180 --> 37:48.599
-[automated voice] Reboot initiated...
-[people clamoring]

37:48.683 --> 37:51.560
-Mr. President, this way, sir!
-[indistinct shouting]

